#### Bootstrapping differences between correlations ####

# Difference between PiCD Dissocial/PSY-5 Aggression and PiCD Dissocial/PSY-5 Disconstraint

sp.r = function(data, indices){
  d = data[indices,]
  cor1 = cor.test(d$dl, d$rfAGGR, method = "spearman")
  cor2 = cor.test(d$dl, d$rfDISC, method = "spearman")
  cor1 = cor1$estimate
  cor2 = cor2$estimate
  cor.diff = cor1 - cor2
  return(cor.diff)
}

set.seed(2019)
boot.r = boot(data = subscales, statistic = sp.r, R = 1000)
boot.ci(boot.r)

# This function estimates a series of multiple regression models with each variable name stored in 'mmpi.var' 
# as the dependent variable ('i').

# Extracting standardized coefficients and putting them into a matrix

models.coef = lapply(picd.mmpi.models, function(x) {
  coef = summ(x, scale = T, transform.response = T, robust = T, digits = 3)$model$coefficients[2:6]
  }) 
models.coef = unlist(models.coef)
models.coef = round(models.coef, 2)
models.coef = matrix(models.coef, ncol = 8) # 5x8 matrix of coefficients, where rows are PiCD scales and
                                            # columns are MMPI-2-RF scales
models.coef = t(models.coef) # Transposing the above 5x8 matrix
rownames(models.coef) = mmpi.var

# P-value adjustment 

models.pvalues = lapply(picd.mmpi.models, function(x){
  p = summ(x, scale = T, transform.response = T, robust = T, digits = 3)$coeftable[20:24]
})
models.pvalues = unlist(models.pvalues)
pvalues.adjust = p.adjust(models.pvalues, method = "BH", n = length(models.pvalues))
pvalues.adjust = round(pvalues.adjust, 3)
pvalues.adjust = matrix(pvalues.adjust, ncol = 8)
pvalues.adjust = t(pvalues.adjust)
rownames(pvalues.adjust) = mmpi.var
colnames(pvalues.adjust) = c("NA", "DT", "DL", "DN", "AN")
